Package com.geolud.atomica.objects

Provides all object classes of the model.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Application
    This class holds information of the application itself like the default game and editor settings and the language to start with.
    AtomToken
    Represents an atom on a field.
    Board
    Defines a game board with a certain number of rows and columns.
    DefaultGameSettings
    Represents the default settings defining a game.
    EditorGameSettings
    Represents the default settings for an editing game.
    Field
    Represents a field on the game board where a token can take place on.
    GameSettings
    Abstract class holding all necessary settings for the initialization of a game situation.
    GameSituation
    This class holds information about a certain game situation, like the arrangement of tokens on the board.
    Help
    Simple class holding the resource information for help files considering the language.
    IndicatorToken
    Represents an indicator on a field.
    Level
    Represents the level a game can be in.
    Molecule
    This class represents molecules made up by atoms.
    Token
    Abstract class representing a token on a field.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Help.HelpLanguage
    The supported languages of the game.
